# Data Grid Rule

All tabular data in the Angular app must use the **data grid tokens** defined in `angular-app/src/styles.scss` (Figma `27686:184938`).

## Sticky header + body scroll (required — global)

Whenever a table can overflow vertically, **only the body rows scroll**. The header must remain visible and must not scroll with the rows.

This applies to every table in the app — page-level lists, defaults settings grids, modals, panels, and nested detail tables.

**Do not** put `overflow-auto` or `overflow-y-auto` on a page body wrapper that contains a table; that scrolls the header away. Scroll happens inside the table frame instead.

### CSS Grid tables (Defaults-style)

Use `data-grid--scroll` and wrap rows / empty state in `data-grid__body`:

```html
<div class="flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden">
  <div class="shrink-0"><!-- section title, filters --></div>

  <div class="data-grid data-grid--scroll min-h-0 flex-1" data-testid="table-example">
    <div class="data-grid__header" style="grid-template-columns: ...">
      <span class="data-grid__header-cell">Name</span>
    </div>

    <div class="data-grid__body">
      <div class="data-grid__empty">No rows yet.</div>
      <ul>
        <li class="data-grid__row" style="grid-template-columns: ...">
          <span class="data-grid__cell">Value</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Multi-row headers (Automations): wrap header rows in `data-grid__header-group` instead of ad hoc `sticky` wrappers.

Embedded tables in scrollable forms may use `data-grid--scroll max-h-[…]` with `data-grid__body`.

### Native `<table>` tables (Shipments, Inventory, Wallet, etc.)

Use `data-grid--scroll` on the scroll container. Sticky `th` styling is global — do **not** add per-column `sticky top-0` classes.

```html
<div class="min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-hidden">
  <div class="data-grid data-grid--scroll min-h-0 h-full">
    <table class="data-grid-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="w-[120px]">Column</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="h-8 hover:bg-surface-light-primary">
          <td>Cell value</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Page layout requirements

- Parent of a scrollable table: `min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-hidden` (not `overflow-auto` on the whole page body).
- Table scroll frame: `data-grid data-grid--scroll min-h-0 flex-1`.
- Page chrome (title bar, footers, section intros): `shrink-0` outside the scroll frame.

## CSS Grid tables (markup reference)

```html
<div class="data-grid" data-testid="table-example">
  <div class="data-grid__header" style="grid-template-columns: ...">
    <span class="data-grid__header-cell">Name</span>
  </div>
  <ul>
    <li class="data-grid__row" style="grid-template-columns: ...">
      <span class="data-grid__cell">Value</span>
      <div class="data-grid__cell data-grid__cell--actions">...</div>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <div class="data-grid__empty">No rows yet.</div>
</div>
```

## Token reference

| Element | Class | Spec |
|---------|-------|------|
| Wrapper | `.data-grid` | White surface, `#E4EAED` border |
| Scroll frame | `.data-grid--scroll` | Fills remaining height; vertical scroll on body or table |
| Scroll body | `.data-grid__body` | Scrollable rows for CSS-grid tables |
| Multi-row header | `.data-grid__header-group` | Sticky group for complex headers |
| Header row | `.data-grid__header` | `#F6F9FB` bg, `#EFF6F9` bottom border, 32px height, sticky |
| Header cell | `.data-grid__header-cell` | 14px bold, `#0B1516`, px-2 |
| Body row | `.data-grid__row` | 32px row, `#E4EAED` divider |
| Body cell | `.data-grid__cell` | 14px regular, `#45565B`, nowrap, fits content |
| Truncate cell | `.data-grid__cell--truncate` | Opt-in ellipsis when crop is acceptable |
| Wrap cell | `.data-grid__cell--wrap` | Explicit multi-line / chip columns only |
| Actions cell | `.data-grid__cell--actions` | Right-align menu/button |
| Empty state | `.data-grid__empty` | Centered, 14px secondary text |
| HTML table | `.data-grid-table` | Same header/cell typography on `th`/`td`; sticky `th` built in |
| Multi-line rows | `.data-grid-table--relaxed` | Taller body rows (panel detail tables) |

## Do not

- Use ad hoc `bg-neutral-100`, `text-sm font-medium`, or `#f6f9fb` on new table headers.
- Put `overflow-auto` on a page body wrapper when the table below should scroll independently.
- Add manual `sticky top-0 z-10` on individual `th` elements (use global `.data-grid-table th`).
- Use `overflow-hidden` on `.data-grid` when rows have action menus (clip risk) — use fixed-position menus.
- Use default truncation or `table-fixed` without verifying column widths — see `16-table-column-sizing.mdc`.

## Row menus

Render dropdowns with **fixed positioning** (see Tags page) when inside scroll/overflow containers.
